The following instruction is ONLY for Ubuntu:

1. pip install django==1.8.2
2. pip install mysqlclient
3. update the jobooking/settings.py's database setting to the following:

DATABASES = {
    'default': {
        'NAME': '',
        'ENGINE': 'django.db.backends.mysql',
        'USER': '',
        'PASSWORD': '',      
    }
}
4. run "python manage.py migrate"
5. pip install django-oauth-toolkit python-social-auth
6. pip install djangorestframework
7. need to make sure the lib requests need to be 2.0.0



Development quite note

sudo apt-get install libffi-dev
sudo apt-get remove python-openssl
sudo pip install pyOpenSSL
sudo  pip install requests==2.0.0 --upgrade


Django
~/Development/jobooking/api/jobooking$ python manage.py runserver
python manage.py makemigrations
python manage.py migrate

python manage.py shell < add_user.py
python manage.py shell < add_category.py 
python manage.py shell < add_image.py
python manage.py shell < add_job.py

curl --dump-header - -H "Accept: application/json" -H "Content-Type: application/json" -X POST --data '{"username":"john","password":"johnpassword","email":"dannyz@gmail.com"}' http://localhost:8000/jobooker/signin
curl -H "Authorization: Bearer xYfbMpadjTaQ3SQYnW1uKc6vNVRrnN" http://localhost:8000/jobs/
curl -H "Authorization: Bearer xYfbMpadjTaQ3SQYnW1uKc6vNVRrnN" http://localhost:8000/jobs/category/



MySql
mysql -uroot -pdannyz jobooking
show tables;
desc jobs_job;
select * from jobs_job;

drop database jobooking;
